settings.subtitle: OUR PROCESS
settings.title: SCREEN PRINTING
settings.text:
SCREENS (MESH STENCILS) ARE USED TO PUSH ONE COLOR AT A TIME ONTO THE APPAREL

FIRST, WE REGISTER THE SCREENS ON TEST SHEETS TO GUARANTEE THE COLORS LINE UP CORRECTLY

THEN, WE PRINT YOUR DESIGN DIRECTLY ONTO YOUR APPAREL, AND RUN IT THROUGH A LARGE DRYER TO CURE THE INKS

settings.title: MORE ABOUT OUR SCREENPRINTING:
settings.text:
- DONE IN BULK AND PERFECT FOR PRODUCING VIVID COLORS AND DESIGNS

- EXAMPLES OF SURFACES WE PRINT ON: SHIRTS, SWEATSHIRTS, JACKETS, HATS, PANTS, TOTE BAGS/PURSES, FLAGS, BANNERS, SIGNS

- DIFFERENT FABRICS: COTTON, POLYESTER, SILK, VISCOSE, ETC. 

- MANY DIFFERENT TYPES OF INK CAN BE USED TO MANIPULATE THE FINAL PRODUCTS AND CREATE CUSTOM EFFECTS

settings.subtitle: OUR PROCESS
settings.title: EMBROIDERY
settings.text: A COMPUTERIZED MACHINE REQUIRING A SPECIFIC FILE TYPE STITCHES DURABLE THREAD INTO THE FABRIC OF YOUR CHOICE TO CREATE CUSTOM DESIGNS, LOGOS, LETTERS, AND MONOGRAMS

settings.title: MORE ABOUT OUR CUSTOM EMBROIDERY
settings.text:
- WE PAY CLOSE ATTENTION TO THE SMALL DETAILS FROM COLOR TO THICKNESS OF THREAD

- EXAMPLES: LOGOS ON HATS, LETTERS ON JACKETS, EMBROIDERY PATCHES, MONOGRAMMED TOWELS, ETC

settings.subtitle: OUR PROCESS
settings.title: CUT & SEW
settings.text:
MANUFACTURE YOUR ENTIRE GARMENT FROM SCRATCH TO ACHIEVE EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANT THE WAY YOU WANT IT

WE HANDLE EVERYTHING FROM IN-HOUSE DESIGN AND CONCEPT CREATION TO FINAL PRODUCT DELIVERY

settings.title: MORE ABOUT OUR CUT & SEW PROCESS:
settings.text:
STEP 1: TELL US ABOUT YOUR CUT AND SEW IDEA WHAT TYPE OF GARMENT: 

- WHAT TYPE OF MATERIAL AND FABRICATION ARE YOU LOOKING FOR?

- HOW MANY PIECES ARE YOU ESTIMATING?

- WHAT IS YOUR DEADLINE?

STEP 2: DESIGN PROCESS

- WORK WITH OUR CREATIVE TEAM TO BUILD A UNIQUE DESIGN

STEP 3: QUOTE & DIGITAL ART APPROVAL

- APPROXIMATE PRICE BASED ON YOUR DESIGN, QUANTITY, AND DEADLINE

STEP 4: SAMPLE MAKING

- SAMPLES CREATED BASED ON REQUESTED MEASUREMENTS AND FINAL TECH PACKS

STEP 5: PRODUCTION

- AFTER SAMPLE IS APPROVED WITH FINAL TECH PACK AND PAYMENT, WE WILL MANUFACTURE THE GARMENTS WITH OUR DESIGNERS, PATTERN MAKERS,  AND PRODUCTION AND QUALITY CONTROL TEAM

STEP 6: SHIPPING & LOGISTICS - WE GOT YOU COVERED. FROM THE START, TO PACKAGING, TO FINAL PRODUCT AT YOUR DOOR

settings.subtitle: OUR PROCESS
settings.title: APPAREL DESIGN
settings.text:
WE CAN HELP DESIGN YOUR LINE!

- CUSTOM GRAPHICS

- TECKPAKS

- COLOR MATCHING 

- FIT SAMPLING

settings.title: MARKETING MATERIALS
settings.text: WE CAN DESIGN AND MANUFACTURE ITEMS TO HELP YOUR BRAND STAND OUT!

settings.subtitle: OUR PROCESS
settings.title: FULFILLMENT
settings.text: WE CONNECT TO YOUR STORE. WE SHIP YOUR PRODUCT DIRECTLY TO YOUR CUSTOMERS.

settings.title: MORE ABOUT OUR FULFILLMENT
settings.text:
STEP 1: CREATE YOUR ONLINE STORE

- IF YOU NEED HELP CREATING AN ONLINE STORE WE CAN HELP. WE RECOMMEND USING SHOPIFY FOR YOUR ONINE STORE.

STEP 2: UPLOAD YOUR PRODUCTS TO YOUR STORE 

- THIS INCLUDES ADDING SKUS TO YOUR PRODUCTS, STYLE NAMES, DESCRIPTIONS AND PRODUCT SHOTS.

STEP 3: SEND US YOUR PRODUCTS

- SHIP US ANY AND ALL PRODUCTS YOU WOULD LIKE US TO FULFILL.

- PLEASE MAKE SURE YOUR PRODUCTS ARE FULFILLMENT READY: BAGGED, TAGGED AND LABELED. PLEASE INCLUDE A PACKING SLIP FOR ALL ITEMS.

STEP 4: CONFIRMATION OF PRODUCTS AND INTEGRATION 

- ONCE WE RECEIVE ALL YOUR PRODUCTS THEY WILL BE CHECKED IN AND INVENTORIED.

- NEXT, WE WILL INTEGRATE OUR SOFTWARE WITH YOUR ONLINE STORE.

STEP 5: START SELLING YOUR PRODUCTS

- WE PICK, PACK AND SHIP YOUR PRODUCTS AS THEY SELL ON YOUR STORE. ADD CUSTOMER SERVICE FOR A COMPLETE HASSLE-FREE EXPERIENCE.

A FASHION FORWARD LIFESTYLE BRAND INSPIRED BY MUSIC & STREET CULTURE. FOUNDED IN 2010, THE RODRIGUEZ BROTHERS ESTABLISHED THE LABEL TO FOLLOW THEIR GRANDPARENTS TRADITION IN THE FASHION INDUSTRY FROM PERU.

"EVERYONE WANTS TO BE A PART OF THE VISION BUT NO ONE WANTS TO BE PART OF THE PROCESS. LIVE FROM WITHIN WHAT YOU BELIEVE YOU WERE BORN FOR. BLESS THOSE WHO CURSE YOU."

settings.title: "Bleeding In Color" TAP02
settings.text: STRATA partners with Miami Based art dealer Marcel Katz founder of The Art Plug to release an eight-piece collection during Art Basel Miami 2019. Each piece is limited to only 50 pieces. "This collection pays homage to my city and is a tribute to my team. The bones represent our core, our foundation, our toughness. Without the bones, the body falls apart. Without my city and my team, I would not be where I am today. Being raised in Miami, Miami culture and the presence of my team & close friends during the course of my career has played a huge part in shaping my values and vision." - Marcel Katz
